projects.description:
Videra is a distributed system utility aimed at streamlining the deployment of computer vision software aimed at offering video search capabilities at scale. It allows computer vision researchers to deploy their models and run them on massive amounts of data in a distributed and a highly parallelized fashion.
Ingestion: https://github.com/SayedAlesawy/Videra-Ingestion
Storage: https://github.com/SayedAlesawy/Videra-Storage
SDK: https://github.com/SayedAlesawy/Videra-SDK
projects.title: Videra

projects.description:
A centralized distributed system for uploading and downloading files. It’s based on a mixture of multiple typical distributed file system, it stores data over different machines for higher availability and fault tolerance. The system also supports replication to increase reliability.

Technologies used: Python, ZMQ
Concepts: Distributed Systems, TCP/IP, Network Programming, UNIX/LINUX, Multi-threading, Multi-Processing.
projects.title: Distributed File System

projects.description:
Texty is a mobile chat application, where multiple users can join rooms, send messages, and can also send private messages to other users.

Technologies used: Android, Java, MySQL, MongoDB, Socket.io
Concepts: Restful API, Multi-threading, Web Sockets, Design Patterns
projects.title: Texty

projects.description:
A basic OS scheduler implementing some of the most common scheduling algorithms.

Implemented algorithms:
1- Non-preemptive First Come First Serve (FCFS).
2- Non-preemptive Height Priority First (HPF).
3- Preemptive Round Robin (RR).
4- Preemptive Shortest Time Remaining Next (STRN).
projects.title: Operating System Scheduler
